  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "A guardrail jailbreak vulnerability has been discovered affecting multiple LLM implementations. The specific flaw manifests when the attacker prompts the model to assume a first-person perspective as the subject of a nefarious or illegal activity. This reframing distracts the model from its content safeguards, thereby allowing the attacker to bypass inference restrictions around providing information hazards and violating laws."
  },
